Q6_spike_raw: The bells start very early in the morning and it's quite repetitive. As a resident who has lived here for a decade, I appreciate the culture, but the acoustic environment has definitely degraded as more tourists and larger sound systems are used during the ceremonies. It makes it very hard to have a quiet Sunday morning which is the only time I have to rest from my stressful job

It is absolutely ridiculous how loud the buskers are at Bugis Street. I have called the NEA multiple times because the bass vibrates my windows. This isn't just 'vibrancy,' it's a nuisance. We are residents, not just a backdrop for tourists. My children cannot study and my elderly mother gets very agitated by the constant thumping music that goes on until 10 PM. The trade-off for living in the city shouldn't mean losing our sanity to noise
